This is the second delivery that updates "get" commands so users can only view
information where they have been granted privileges.  This delivery handles:

get components;
get privileges on component;
get privileges on component for <role>;
get privileges on component for <user> [cascade];
  cascade returns privileges for user plus any roles the user has been granted

…ation in new format

Currently SET STATISTICS ON | OFF alone is supported. It is improved to take some more options

SET STATISTICS PERTABLE ;
SET STATISTICS PROGRESS ;
SET STATISTICS DEFAULT ;
This will display pertable, progress, operator level statistics for the these options respectively.

SET STATISTICS ALL will display both progress and operator level statistics.

These commands are valid both in sqlci and trafci.

APIs used to clear compiler caches had changed, leading to syntax errors.

Modified the following -
DELETE ALL FROM TABLE(QUERYCACHE());
to
DELETE ALL FROM TABLE(QUERYCACHE('ALL','LOCAL'));
